    {
      "id": "/page/1/Text/11",
      "block_type": "Text",
      "html": "<p block-type=\"Text\">Observe that the Kelly strategy has enormous returns most of the time, but it is possible to make <math display=\"inline\">700</math> independent bets, all with a <math display=\"inline\">14\\%</math> advantage at differing odds, and lose 98% of one's fortune. So the Kelly strategy, which is used by many great investors (see <math display=\"inline\">[14]</math>) is risky in the short term because the absolute Arrow-Pratt risk aversion index is almost zero; it is also risky in the long term and must be used with care.</p>",
